{code:java}
 { _your code snippet_ }{code}

At current when Jira Cloud instance get integrated with Code repository (e.g. GitHub, Bitbucket) a custom field "Development" appears which contains not consistent information that might be more misleading (giving false positives) then useful. It is observed when issues data get collected as bulk list from REST API search (GET /rest/api/2/search ) in attempt to aggregate pull requests of commits.

It turns out that "Development" field contains either "pull requests" information or "commits" which prevents accurate aggregation for list of  issues because the status of Development properties is just partial even worse. The provided commits number exclude the one included in pull requests.

The only workaround which *extremely inefficient*  and not an option from performance perspective is to call for each issue in the list one or more of following routes:
{code:java}
rest/dev-status/1.0/issue/summary?issueId=<ID>

/rest/dev-status/1.0/issue/detail?issueId=<ID>&applicationType=github&dataType=pullrequest

/rest/dev-status/1.0/issue/detail?issueId=<ID>&applicationType=github&dataType=repository
{code}
 

*Expected:*
 Within "Development" field is expected to be stored actual state info of all commits, pull requests, repos, branches associated with the issue like the one returned from rest/dev-status/1.0/issue/summary?issueId=<ID>.**

 

*Details for the inconsistency of data:*
 Here is example info extracted from Development field

after Pull Requests execution (missing number of commits)

 
{code:java}
"customfield_10000": "{pullrequest={dataType=pullrequest, state=MERGED, stateCount=1}, json={\"cachedValue\":{\"errors\":[],\"summary\":{\"pullrequest\":{\"overall\":{\"count\":1,\"lastUpdated\":\"2018-07-30T13:33:54.000+0300\",\"stateCount\":1,\"state\":\"MERGED\",\"dataType\":\"pullrequest\",\"open\":false},\"byInstanceType\":{\"github\":{\"count\":1,\"name\":\"GitHub\"}}}}},\"isStale\":false}}",{code}
 

after Commit (missing number of pull requests)

 
{code:java}
"customfield_10000": "{repository={count=10, dataType=repository}, json={\"cachedValue\":{\"errors\":[],\"summary\":{\"repository\":{\"overall\":{\"count\":10,\"lastUpdated\":\"2018-08-04T23:59:10.000+0300\",\"dataType\":\"repository\"},\"byInstanceType\":{\"github\":{\"count\":10,\"name\":\"GitHub\"}}}}},\"isStale\":false}}"{code}

h3. Summary
We noticed that there seems to be an error shown when moving the issue to a backlog.
Using developer tools (F12), it shows the error as :

{code}
{{"errorMessages":[],"errors":{"summary":"Field 'summary' cannot be set. It is not on the appropriate screen, or unknown."}}
{code}

However, user has discovered that this is related to permission issue rather than "not on appropriate screen".

Perhaps it would be best to log the error message to show the proper error message.

